descr: "The MeasureReport resource contains the results of evaluating a measure."

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this report when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance."

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The report status. No data will be available until the report status is complete."

fields.name: type
fields.descr: "The type of measure report. This may be an individual report, which provides a single patient's score for the measure; a patient listing, which returns the list of patients that meet the various criteria in the measure; or a summary report, which returns a population count for each of the criteria in the measure."

fields.name: measure
fields.descr: "A reference to the Measure that was evaluated to produce this report."

fields.name: patient
fields.descr: "Optional Patient if the report was requested for a single patient."

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date this measure report was generated."

fields.name: period
fields.descr: "The reporting period for which the report was calculated."

fields.name: group
fields.descr: "The results of the calculation, one for each population group in the measure."

fields.name: evaluatedResources
fields.descr: "A reference to a Bundle containing the Resources that were used in the evaluation of this report."

fields.name: text
fields.descr:
"A human-readable narrative that contains a summary of the resource, and may be used to represent the content of the resource to a human. The narrative need not encode all the structured data, but is required to contain sufficient detail to make it \"clinically safe\" for a human to just read the narrative. Resource definitions may define what content should be represented in the narrative to ensure clinical safety."
